---
const steps = [
  {
    num: '01',
    title: 'Install APM',
    accent: 'var(--signal-architecture)',
    description: 'One-line install of the Agent Package Manager. Works on macOS, Linux, and Windows.',
    code: '$ curl -sSL https://aka.ms/apm-unix | sh',
  },
  {
    num: '02',
    title: 'Install the skill',
    accent: 'var(--signal-process)',
    description: 'Inside the repo you want to retrofit, declare ai-tooling as a project dep and compile. This stages the apm-retrofit skill into .claude/ (or .github/, .cursor/, etc.) so your agent picks it up.',
    code: '$ cd your-repo && apm init -y\n$ apm install \\\n    thinkjones/awesome-apm-stacks/ai-tooling\n$ apm compile',
  },
  {
    num: '03',
    title: 'Retrofit your repo',
    accent: 'var(--signal-measure)',
    description: 'From inside your skills repo, invoke the skill. It inventories every primitive, proposes an apm.yml, and dry-runs the result before you commit.',
    code: '> /apm-retrofit\n\n✓ found 4 primitives\n✓ wrote apm.yml\n✓ apm install --dry-run OK',
  },
];
---

<section id="retrofit" class="py-24 relative">
  <div class="container-wide relative">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-16">
      <span class="section-label">// For Skill Authors</span>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-headline-lg md:text-display-md tracking-tighter text-text-primary mb-4">
        Already maintain a skills repo?<br />Make it APM-compliant in three steps.
      </h2>
      <div class="section-divider"></div>
      <p class="text-body-lg text-text-secondary">
        Microsoft APM ships <code class="font-mono text-body-md">apm init</code>, but it's deliberately minimal — it drops a stub manifest without looking at what's actually in your repo. The
        <a href="https://github.com/thinkjones/awesome-apm-stacks/tree/main/ai-tooling" class="underline decoration-brand-orange/40 hover:decoration-brand-orange" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ai-tooling</a>
        package fills that gap. The <code class="font-mono text-body-md">apm-retrofit</code> skill walks your repo, classifies every SKILL.md, plugin.json, AGENTS.md, MCP manifest, hook, command, and sub-agent it finds, then proposes a correctly-shaped <code class="font-mono text-body-md">apm.yml</code> for you to review.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
      {steps.map(({ num, title, description, code, accent }) => (
        <div class="sculptural-panel flex flex-col h-full">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
            <span class="font-mono text-label-sm uppercase tracking-widest" style={`color: ${accent}`}>{num}</span>
            <span class="h-px flex-1" style={`background: ${accent}; opacity: 0.4`}></span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-headline-sm tracking-tighter text-text-primary mb-3">{title}</h3>
          <p class="text-body-md text-text-secondary mb-6 flex-1">{description}</p>
          <pre class="font-mono text-body-sm bg-bg-secondary/60 border border-border p-4 text-text-primary leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code>{code}</code></pre>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="sculptural-panel">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <span class="mt-2 w-6 h-px bg-brand-orange shrink-0"></span>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-headline-sm tracking-tighter text-text-primary mb-3">
            What the skill actually does
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body-md text-text-secondary mb-4">
            It inventories primitives from every layout APM recognises — root <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">SKILL.md</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">skills/*/SKILL.md</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">.claude/</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">.github/plugin/</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">.cursor-plugin/</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">.mcp.json</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">hooks.json</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">commands/</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">agents/</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">AGENTS.md</code>, <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">CLAUDE.md</code>. It auto-detects <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">target:</code> from the directories present, infers <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">type:</code> from the primitive mix, and derives <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">name</code>/<code class="font-mono text-body-sm">version</code>/<code class="font-mono text-body-sm">description</code> from existing signals — never inventing values.
          </p>
          <p class="text-body-md text-text-secondary">
            Before writing, it diffs against any existing <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">apm.yml</code> and asks for confirmation. After writing, it validates with <code class="font-mono text-body-sm">apm install --dry-run</code>. It never deletes existing files. It never pushes anything.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
